"# Appendix A ‚Äî CORE Verb Cheat Sheet

The verbs you'll reach for most often, grouped by topic. Not every CORE verb is listed ‚Äî for the complete list, see the reference (Appendix F).

## Arithmetic
- `+ - * /` ‚Äî the four basics. Variadic. `(+)` = 0, `(*)` = 1.
- `abs` ‚Äî absolute value.
- `min max` ‚Äî pick the smallest/largest of any arguments.
- `modulo quotient remainder` ‚Äî integer division bits.
- `expt` ‚Äî power. `(expt 2 8)` = 256.

## Math module
- `math/sqrt math/pow math/floor math/ceil math/round`
- `math/lerp a b t` ‚Äî linear interpolation
- `math/clamp x lo hi` ‚Äî force into range
- `math/sum math/avg` ‚Äî over lists
- `const/pi const/tau const/e const/phi`
- `geom/sin geom/cos geom/tan` ‚Äî trig in radians
- `geom/->radians geom/->degrees`
- `geom/distance p1 p2`

## Comparison
- `= < > <= >=` ‚Äî numeric
- `equal?` ‚Äî deep equality for lists, strings, numbers
- `eq?` ‚Äî pointer equality (same object)
- `zero? positive? negative? odd? even?`

## Boolean
- `and or not` ‚Äî logic. `and`/`or` are macros; short-circuit.
- `#t #f` ‚Äî true/false literals.

## Variables / bindings
- `define` ‚Äî bind a name
- `set!` ‚Äî change an existing binding
- `let let* letrec` ‚Äî local bindings
- `let loop ((var val)) body` ‚Äî named let for loops

## Functions
- `lambda (args) body` ‚Äî nameless function
- `define (f args) body` ‚Äî sugar for `(define f (lambda ...))`
- `apply f lst` ‚Äî call `f` with elements of `lst` as arguments
- `. rest` in arg list ‚Äî variable-arity

## Control flow
- `if cond then else` ‚Äî the branch
- `cond (test1 body1) ... (else default)` ‚Äî many branches
- `case value ((v1 v2) body) ...` ‚Äî dispatch by value
- `when cond body ...` ‚Äî one-way branch (macro)
- `unless cond body ...` ‚Äî inverted when
- `begin body ...` ‚Äî sequence, return last

## Lists
- `list` ‚Äî build a list from arguments
- `'(1 2 3)` ‚Äî literal list
- `car cdr` ‚Äî first / rest
- `cadr caddr cddr` ‚Äî deeper access
- `cons` ‚Äî prepend to a list
- `length reverse append`
- `list-ref lst n` ‚Äî nth element
- `member x lst` ‚Äî find x, return tail from that point
- `assoc key alist` ‚Äî find pair by first element
- `null? pair?` ‚Äî predicates
- `range a b` ‚Äî list of integers [a, b)

## Higher-order
- `map f lst` ‚Äî transform each item
- `filter pred lst` ‚Äî keep passing items
- `reduce f init lst` ‚Äî combine into one value
- `for-each f lst` ‚Äî side-effect over each item

## Strings
- `string-append` ‚Äî concatenate
- `string-length` ‚Äî count characters
- `string->list list->string`
- `string->number number->string`
- `string->symbol symbol->string`

## Type predicates
- `number? string? symbol? procedure? pair? null? list?`

## I/O
- `display value` ‚Äî print without newline
- `newline` ‚Äî print a newline
- `write value` ‚Äî print in read-back form

## Randomness
- `random n` ‚Äî float in [0, n)
- `random-int n` ‚Äî integer in [0, n)
- `randint a b` ‚Äî integer in [a, b)
- `random-pick lst` ‚Äî pick one element
- `random-range lo hi` ‚Äî float in [lo, hi)
- `with-seed n body` ‚Äî deterministic randomness

## Grid graphics
- `grid-init cols rows` ‚Äî set up a grid
- `grid/dot col row color` ‚Äî paint one cell
- `grid/clear` ‚Äî wipe
- `grid/glow col row intensity` ‚Äî with a glow color
- `cols rows` ‚Äî dimensions
- `pixels-wide pixels-tall` ‚Äî pixel dimensions

## Sprites
- `sprite name x y color` ‚Äî push a sprite spec
- `sprites` ‚Äî the current sprite list

## Entities (name-addressable things in the world)
- `entity/make id x y w h` ‚Äî create
- `entity/set-pos! id x y` ‚Äî teleport
- `entity/set-vel! id vx vy` ‚Äî set persistent velocity
- `entity/x id  entity/y id  entity/pos id  entity/state id`
- `entity/despawn! id` ‚Äî remove
- `entity/overlaps? a b` ‚Äî collision test
- `entity/alive? id`

## World
- `world/spawn kind x y w h` ‚Äî like entity/make but returns unique id
- `world/step` ‚Äî one physics tick
- `world/reset!` ‚Äî clear entities
- `world/gravity! g` ‚Äî set gravity
- `world/count` ‚Äî how many entities
- `world/collisions` ‚Äî list of colliding pairs
- `world/impulse! id vx vy` ‚Äî one-frame velocity change

## Audio
- `audio/play kind arg ...` ‚Äî dispatch: 'tone freq dur, 'note name dur, etc.
- `audio/tempo bpm?` ‚Äî get/set
- `audio/halt` ‚Äî stop and clear
- `audio/playing?` ‚Äî bool
- `note/strike pitch dur` ‚Äî play a single note
- `note/place-at pitch offset dur` ‚Äî schedule at time
- `synth/play patch pitch dur`
- `synth/chord notes dur` ‚Äî play list of notes together
- `synth/kit name` ‚Äî drum hit ('kick, 'snare, 'hat, 'clap, 'crash)

## Frames / animation
- `on-frame handler` ‚Äî install frame handler
- `frame` ‚Äî current frame number
- `begin-frame end-frame` ‚Äî mark frame boundaries

## Cortex (persistent memory)
- `cortex/write key value` ‚Äî save persistently
- `cortex/read key` ‚Äî read; #f if missing
- `cortex/keys cortex/size` ‚Äî inspect
- `cortex/forget key` ‚Äî remove
- `cortex/remember cortex/recall` ‚Äî session-only (in-memory)

## Time
- `time/now` ‚Äî current wall time
- `time/delta since` ‚Äî elapsed since

## Vectors (2D)
- `vec/make x y` ‚Äî make a vector
- `vec/+ vec/- vec/add vec/sub`
- `vec/norm v` ‚Äî magnitude
- `vec/normalize v` ‚Äî unit vector
- `vec/distance a b`
- `vec/dot vec/scale vec/lerp`

## Assertions
- `assert/check-with pred value` ‚Äî verify

## Macros
- `define-syntax` + `syntax-rules ()` ‚Äî define a macro
- `,expand form` in the REPL ‚Äî see what a macro expanded to

## System introspection
- `system/health` ‚Äî runtime status
- `system/registry` ‚Äî list of registered verbs

---

To see help for any verb from the REPL:

```
$ motoi repl
motoi> ,help audio/play
```

For the full reference, see `scheme/MOTOI-SCHEME-REFERENCE.slat` in your Motoi installation, or Appendix F of this book for how to read it.")
